Setup
--------

Pretty simple:

    > git clone git@github.com:csinchok/Twitter-Roulette.git twitter-roulette
    > cd twitter-roulette
    > python2.7 bootstrap.py
    > bin/buildout
    > bin/syncdb
    > bin/buildout

You'll need to add a "social_keys.py" to the "twitterroulette" directory. This file should contain:

TWITTER_CONSUMER_KEY         = 'GET THIS FROM TWITTER'
TWITTER_CONSUMER_SECRET      = 'GET THIS FROM TWITTER'

Then run your server:

    > bin/django runserver

If you change the model, make sure you make a migration file and migrate:

    > bin/django schemamigration roulette --all
    > bin/django migrate

That's about it.